gang Peterson  An adaptation of Homer's great epic, the film follows the assault on Troy by the united Greek forces and chronicles the fates of the men involved.  Click here for more info on this film at IMDb.    Orfeo Negro (1959) Black Orpheus  Wed, Feb 26, 2019 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm  Directed by Marcel Camus  A retelling of the Orpheus and Eurydice myth, set during the time of the Carnaval in Rio de Janeiro.  Click here for more info on this film at IMDb.    I, Claudius (1976) 2 episodes  Wed, Mar 11, 2019 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm  Directed by Herbert Wise  The history of the Roman Empire as experienced by one of its rulers.  Click here for more info on this film at IMDb.    Sign of the Cross (1932)  Wed, Apr 8, 2019 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm  Directed by Cecil B. DeMille  A Roman soldier becomes torn between his love for a Christian woman and his loyalty to Emperor Nero.  Click here for more info on this film at IMDb.    Gladiator (2000)  Wed, Apr 22, 2019 3:00 pm - 5:00 pm  Directed by Ridley Scott  A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.  Click here for more info on this film at IMDb.          Past Semester's Films     Fall 2019         Fall 2019    Clash of the Titans (1981)  Spartacus (1960)  I, Claudius (1976)  A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum (1966)  Chi-Raq (2015)         Spring 2019         Spring 2019    Rockules (2013)  Clash of the Titan’s (1988)  Spartacus (1960)  Rome (2015)  I, Claudius (1976)  Agora (2009)                 Events    Back to main content           Schedule of Events    Conversation Hours     Arabic Conversation Hour    Chinese Conversation Hour    French Conversation Hour    German Conversation Hour (SprachCafe)    Italian Conversation Hour (Piazza Italia)    Japanese Conversation Hour    Spanish Conversation Hour      Film Series     Ancient World, Modern Media    Central & Eastern European Film Club      Special Events             Classics and Mediterranean Studies  The Department of Classics and Mediterranean Studies is part of the School of Literatures, Cultural Studies and Linguistics and offers language courses: Latin, Arabic and Modern Greek. Click here to find out more about this department!      College of Liberal Arts and Sciences  As the largest undergraduate college at UIC, the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences (LAS) offers a diverse community of actively engaged scholars and students across the natural sciences, social sciences, and humanities, as well as interdisciplinary and pre-professional areas of study.      Film Series  Interested in attending a Film Series event in your favorite language? Check the schedule here! All film screenings are available to the public, and we provide tea, coffee, & fresh popcorn too!      Contact Us  Do you want to schedule an event in the Language Oasis? Do you need help with a technology tool or want to schedule a workshop? Contact us with any questions you may have!                  UIC Logo         Language  And Culture  Learning Center  College of  Liberal Arts  And  Sciences         Contact   Language and Culture Learning Center  703 South Morgan St., 301 GH Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996 2119  lclc@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 